{"title_page": "2020 Philippine coronavirus testing controversy", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Philippine English|date=April 2020}}\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines}}\n<!---Undue weight to the list, as per AFD consensus. Consensus is to reframe the article to focus on the testing controversy itself. See talk page for discussion--->\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Undue weight|date=April 2020}}{{Cleanup|reason=Reframe the article to give more focus to the COVID-19 testing controversy itself rather than listing every tested public figure as per the [[Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/List of Philippine public figures who underwent COVID-19 testing|1st Articles for deletion]] discussion|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n\nThe '''coronavirus testing controversy''' is an ongoing controversy involving several government officials who were reported in media to have been [[COVID-19 testing|tested for coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19) in the first months of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines|coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines\u200e]], supposedly bypassing the triage algorithm which was set up by the [[Department of Health (Philippines)|Department of Health]] (DOH).  \n\nAt the time, the DOH had set up the triage algorithm as a way to maximize resources, given the scarcity of COVID-19 test kits and the limited number of laboratories capable of processing the test results.  In some instances, the controversy extended to family members of these government officials, which had also been given early COVID-19 testing despite the algorithm.\n\n== Background ==\n=== Scarcity of laboratories and test kits ===\n{{further|Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Philippines}}\nThe Philippine government did not have the capacity to test for the [[SARS-CoV-2]] virus until January 30, 2020, when the government-run [[Research Institute for Tropical Medicine]] (RITM) was finally able to run confirmatory tests. Until that date, samples from suspected COVID-19 cases had to be sent to Victorian Infectious Diseases Reference Laboratory in [[Melbourne]], Australia for testing.<ref name=\"phacquires\">{{cite news |title=PH acquires confirmatory test kits for novel coronavirus |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/1/29/Novel-coronavirus-confirmatory-test-kits-primers-RITM.html |publisher=CNN |date=January 29, 2020}}</ref> \n\nHowever, there were still very few testing kits in the Philippines, and the RITM was still the only laboratory that had the ability to process test results. By March 9, 2020, only 200 to 250 tests could be processed per day.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Magtulis |first1=Prinz |title=With only 250 people tested a day, Philippine health sector appears ill-prepared for COVID-19 |url=https://www.philstar.com/business/2020/03/09/1999444/only-250-people-tested-day-philippine-health-sector-appears-ill-prepared-covid-19 |accessdate=March 13, 2020 |work=The Philippine Star |date=March 9, 2020}}</ref>  \n\nBy March 23, 2020 the number had gone up to almost 1000 a day, as new laboratories gained the capacity to process test results and various entities donated about 100,000 test kits to the RITM.  But the Philippines' overall capacity to do COVID-19 testing was still very limited given the national spread of the disease.<ref name=\"dohsends100k\">{{cite news |title=DOH sends 100,000 test kits to RITM, testing centers nationwide |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/23/Coronavirus-Philippines-test-kits-testing-centers.html |accessdate=March 23, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 14, 2020, the Philippines' national government began \"progressive mass testing\" for COVID-19<ref name=\"CNNProgressiveMassTesting\">{{Cite web |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/4/14/Philippines-COVID-19-mass-testing.html |title=PH begins 'progressive' COVID-19 mass testing |website=cnn |language=en |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414052020/https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/4/14/Philippines-COVID-19-mass-testing.html |archive-date=2020-04-14 |access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> after it received \"tens of thousands of testing kits\" from  various donor countries,<ref name=\"BidabidangSG\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/virus-deaths-spike-ahead-of-mass-testing-in-philippines |title=Coronavirus deaths spike ahead of mass testing in Philippines |last=Dancel |first=Raul |date=2020-04-13 |website=The Straits Times |language=en |access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> and SARS-COV-2 test kits produced by the [[University of the Philippines]]' Philippine Genome Center became available.<ref name=\"RhiaUPTestKits\">{{Cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/ancx/culture/spotlight/03/14/20/meet-the-filipino-scientist-who-invented-the-low-cost-covid-19-testing-kits |title=Meet the Filipino scientist who invented the low-cost COVID-19 testing kits |last=Diomampo-Grana |first=Rhia |website=ABS-CBN News |access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>  To process these tests, the DOH reported that \"dozens of testing laboratories\" would come online within the month.<ref name=\"BidabidangSG\"/>\n\n=== Philippine triage decision algorithm ===\nAs soon as the government gained the ability to conduct COVID-19 tests locally, they developed a [[triage]] algorithm which would serve as a \"decision tool.\" This would determine which patients would be allowed to use the few available test kits, and the processing time of the few Philippine laboratories capable of doing COVID-19 tests.<ref name=\"AlgorithmAO20200130\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.doh.gov.ph/sites/default/files/health-update/COVID-19-Advisory-No2.pdf |title=Decision Tool for Novel Coronavirus Assessment for Bureau of Quarantine and Hospitals (Version as of January 30, 2020) |date=January 30, 2020 |website=Government of the Philippines Department of Health}}</ref>\n\nThe algorithm sorted people into \"[[Patient Under Investigation|patients under investigation]]\" (PUI), who would be given tests; and \"persons under monitoring\" (PUM), who would not be tested, but rather told to go into a 14-day self quarantine.<ref name=\"AlgorithmAO20200130\"/>\n\n== Prioritized testing of government officials ==\n{{see also|Cacique Democracy}}\nWhile some VIPs were legitimately on the priority list for testing, some of them who were not PUIs did not follow the [[medical guideline|medical protocol]] outlined by [[Department of Health (Philippines)|Department of Health]]'s [[triage|triage algorithm]] and were tested ahead of the [[symptomatic]] people who were in the priority list, hence the [[Very important person|VIP]] treatment controversy.<ref name=\"DOHTriageAlgorithm\">{{cite web |title=Algorithm for Triage of Patients with Possible COVID-19 Infection in Healthcare Facilities |url=https://www.facebook.com/OfficialDOHgov/photos/a.157979910879936/3135067276504503/?type=3&theater |website=[[Facebook]] |publisher=[[Department of Health (Philippines)|Department of Health]] |accessdate=March 23, 2020|date=March 10, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\">{{cite news |last1=Malasig |first1=Jeline |title=A closer look at DOH's triage system and why politicians, officials are getting tested for COVID-19 |url=https://www.interaksyon.com/politics-issues/2020/03/19/164632/closer-look-at-dohs-triage-system-and-why-politicians-are-getting-tested-for-covid-19/ |publisher=[[Interaksyon]] |date=March 19, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/27/20/makati-village-urges-pacquiao-family-to-self-quarantine-senator-says-will-always-follow-the-law |title=Makati village urges Pacquiao, family to self-quarantine; senator says 'will always follow the law'|date=March 27, 2020 |publisher=ABS-CBN News}}</ref><ref name=\"covid19confusioninPH\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/in-depth/255403-agonizing-confusion-coronavirus-testing-philippines |title=Hell on Earth: The agonizing confusion over coronavirus testing in PH |last=Cepeda |first=Mara |date=March 22, 2020 |website=Rappler.com}}</ref> This included family members and the staff of current and former government officials.<ref name=\"philstarBongbongLiza\">{{cite news |title=Bongbong Marcos' family, staff take COVID-19 tests which turn out negative |url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2020/03/26/2003570/bongbong-marcos-family-staff-take-covid-19-tests-which-turn-out-negative |publisher=[[The Philippine Star]] |date=March 26, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"gmaStatementBongbongWife\">{{cite news |last1=Garcia |first1=Ma. Angelica |title=Statement allegedly from Bongbong Marcos' wife says they got COVID-19 test results in a day |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/nation/731443/statement-allegedly-from-bongbong-marcos-wife-says-they-got-covid-19-test-results-in-a-day/story/ |publisher=[[GMA News Online]] |date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe DOH later issued a statement saying that these tests were a \"courtesy\" rather than a \"VIP treatment\" saying that \"there is no policy for VIP treatment and that all specimens are being processed on a first-in, first-out basis with courtesy accorded to officials holding positions of national security and public health.\"<ref name=\"LaraTanCourtesyTesting\">{{Cite news |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/23/Senator-Tito-Sotto-coronavirus-COVID-19-test.html |title=Health Dept. gives COVID-19 testing 'courtesy' to officials involved in nat'l security, public health |date=March 29, 2020|publisher=CNN Philippines|last=Tan|first=Lara}}</ref>\n\n== List of government officials who underwent COVID-19 testing ==\n{{Prose|date=April 2020}}\nThe following is a list of Philippine public figures, along with their immediate family members and staff, who were [[COVID-19 testing|tested]] for the [[coronavirus disease 2019]] and publicly disclosed it.\n\n<!-- Kindly arrange entries alphabetically by last name -->\n=== Executive ===\n==== National government ====\n* President [[Rodrigo Duterte]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonPoliticiansFamilies\" /><ref name=\"gmaDuterteGoNoCovid\">{{cite news |last1=Cordero |first1=Ted |title=Duterte, Go have no COVID-19 infection, tests show |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/nation/729606/duterte-go-have-no-covid-19-infection-tests-show/story/ |publisher=[[GMA News Online]] |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"philstarZubiriPositive\" /><ref name=\"manilaTimesDuterteFamily\">{{cite news |last1=Valente |first1=Catherine S. |title=Duterte family undergoes Covid-19 test |url=https://www.manilatimes.net/2020/03/17/news/latest-stories/duterte-family-undergoes-covid-19-test/703891/ |publisher=[[The Manila Times]] |date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n* Executive Secretary [[Salvador Medialdea]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"PalaceStatementOfficialsNegative\">{{cite news |last1=Geducos  |first1=Argyll Cyrus |title=Palace: Medialdea, Durante, other gov\u2019t officials test negative for COVID-19 |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/22/baste-duterte-tests-negative-for-covid-19/ |publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n* Interior and Local Government Secretary Eduardo A\u00f1o&nbsp;\u2013 positive<ref>{{cite web |last=Fermin|first=Margret|title=Cesar Virata, martial law prime minister infected with COVID-19|date=April 1, 2020|url=https://philippineslifestyle.com/cesar-virata-martial-law-prime-minister-infected-with-covid-19/ |publisher=Philippine Lifestyle News}}</ref>\n* Budget Secretary [[Wendel Avisado]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"gmaNoHouseMember\">{{cite news |title=Cayetano: No House member under self-quarantine exhibiting symptoms of COVID-19 |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/news/nation/729884/cayetano-no-house-member-under-self-quarantine-exhibiting-symptoms-of-covid-19/story/ |date=March 16, 2020 |ref=[[GMA News Online]]}}</ref>\n* Transportation Secretary [[Arthur Tugade]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"interaksyonPoliticiansFamilies\" /><ref name=\"gmaNoHouseMember\" />\n* Finance Secretary [[Carlos Dominguez]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"PalaceStatementOfficialsNegative\"/>\n* Public Works Secretary [[Mark Villar]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"PalaceStatementOfficialsNegative\"/>\n\n==== Governors ====\n* [[Jonvic Remulla]] ([[Cavite]])&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"No to VIP testing \" /><ref name=\"interaksyonOfficialsIssuingApologies\"/><ref name=\"yahooRemulla\">{{cite news |title=Asymptomatic Cavite Governor says sorry for taking COVID-19 test amid shortage |url=https://ph.news.yahoo.com/asymptomatic-cavite-governor-says-sorry-065444465.html |agency=Coconuts Manila |publisher=[[Yahoo News]] |date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n:Asymptomatic, acknowledged bypassing the DOH's protocol and triage testing algorithm, apologized to public.\n\n==== Mayors ====\n* [[Leopoldo Bataoil]] ([[Lingayen]], [[Pangasinan]])&nbsp;\u2013 negative. Had persistent cough and was exposed to the Filipina who tested positive in Australia.<ref name=\"absCbnLingayen\">{{cite news |title=Lingayen mayor tests negative for coronavirus |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/10/20/lingayen-mayor-tests-negative-for-coronavirus |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Philip Crispino]] ([[Caba, La Union]])&nbsp;\u2013 positive<ref name=\"absCbnLaUnion\">{{cite news |last1=Ilao |first1=Micaella |title=La Union town mayor, councilor positive for COVID-19 |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/21/20/la-union-town-mayor-councilor-positive-for-covid-19 |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ferdie Estrella ([[Baliuag, Bulacan]])&nbsp;\u2013 positive<ref name=\"inqBulacanMayor\">{{cite news |last1=Galvez |first1=Daphne |title=Bulacan mayor tests positive for COVID-19 |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1243666/bulacan-mayor-tests-positive-for-covid-19 |publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] |date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n* Joric Garula ([[Taytay, Rizal]]) \u2013 positive<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/29/Taytay-Mayor-Joric-Gacula-tests-positive-COVID-19.html|title=Taytay, Rizal mayor tests positive for COVID-19|date=March 29, 2020|work=CNN Philippines|access-date=March 29, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Isko Moreno]] ([[Manila City]])&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"absCbnIsko\">{{cite news |title=Manila Mayor Isko Moreno tests negative for COVID-19 |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/15/20/manila-mayor-isko-moreno-tests-negative-for-covid-19 |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"philstarIsko\">{{cite news |last1=Galupo |first1=Rey |title=Isko undergoes testing for coronavirus |url=https://www.philstar.com/nation/2020/03/13/2000326/isko-undergoes-testing-coronavirus |publisher=[[Philippine Star]] |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n:* Cesar Chavez (Moreno's chief of staff), other city hall officials who accompanied mayor during trip to [[London]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarIsko\" />\n\n==== Vice mayors ====\n* [[Sebastian Duterte]] ([[Davao City]])&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"manilaTimesDuterteFamily\" /><ref name=\"mbBaste\">{{cite news |last1=Colina IV |first1=Antonio |title='Baste' Duterte tests negative for COVID-19 |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/22/baste-duterte-tests-negative-for-covid-19/ |publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=March 22, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"presidentialfamily\"/>\n\n=== Legislative ===\n==== Senate ====\nThe Senate held a hearing concerning the Committee on Basic Education, Arts and Culture on March 5, 2020 where a resource person later tested positive for COVID-19.<ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\"/>\n*[[Nancy Binay]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonPoliticiansFamilies\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonOfficialsIssuingApologies\"/><ref name=\"yahooRemulla\" /><ref name=\"absCbnBinayGatchalian\">{{cite news |last1=Domingo |first1=Katrina |title=Binay, Gatchalian test negative for coronavirus |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/17/20/gatchalian-tests-negative-for-covid-19 |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Pia Cayetano]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\">{{cite news |last1=Terrazola |first1=Vanne Elaine |title=Six more senators undergo COVID-19 test |url=https://news.mb.com.ph/2020/03/17/six-more-senators-undergo-covid-19-test/ |publisher=[[Manila Bulletin]] |date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Franklin Drilon]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative. Wife also negative.<ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n* [[Sherwin Gatchalian]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonPoliticiansFamilies\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonOfficialsIssuingApologies\"/><ref name=\"yahooRemulla\" /><ref name=\"absCbnBinayGatchalian\" />\n* [[Bong Go]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"gmaDuterteGoNoCovid\" /><ref name=\"philstarZubiriPositive\" /><ref name=\"BongGo\">{{Cite news |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/26/20/go-to-self-quarantine-after-exposure-to-coronavirus-infected-congressman |title=Go to self-quarantine after exposure to coronavirus-infected congressman |date=March 26, 2020 }}</ref>\n* [[Richard J. Gordon|Dick Gordon]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n* [[Panfilo Lacson]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" /><ref name=\"dzbbLacsonandSotto\">{{cite news |last1=de la Pe\u00f1a |first1=Weng |title=LIVESTREAM: Dobol B sa News TV Livestream: March 22, 2020 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c9l7Cnaeo9I&t=8480 |publisher=[[DZBB-AM]] |date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Imee Marcos]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n* [[Manny Pacquiao]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative <ref name=\"Pacquiao\" >{{cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/28/20/pacquiao-tests-negative-coronavirus |title=Quarantined Pacquiao says negative for coronavirus after rapid test |date=March 28, 2020 |publisher=ABS-CBN News}}</ref>\n:He said he received a rapid testing kit from friends from South Korea, though not approved by the Food and Drug Administration.\n* [[Grace Poe]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n* [[Bong Revilla]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n* [[Tito Sotto]]&nbsp;\u2013 tested twice. 1st test negative. 2nd test {{small|TBA}}<ref name=\"philstarTolentino\" /><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" /><ref name=\"dzbbLacsonandSotto\" />\n: Sotto said that the first test was made using a kit not accredited by the DOH. He subsequently took a second test, this time using a DOH-accredited kit after he began exhibitng dry cough and sore throat.<ref name=\"vipsenatorclarify\">{{cite news |last1=Tan |first1=Lara |title=VIP treatment? Senators clarify their use of COVID-19 test kits amid backlash |url=https://www.cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/23/Senator-Tito-Sotto-coronavirus-COVID-19-test.html |accessdate=March 23, 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=March 23, 2020}}</ref> Stated that he was willing to take a 3rd test after exposure to Rep. Eric Go Yap.<ref name=\"absCbnTitoSottoAnotherTest\">{{cite news |title=Sotto willing to take another COVID-19 test after exposure to Rep. Yap |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/03/26/20/sotto-willing-to-take-another-covid-19-test-after-exposure-to-rep-yap |publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]] |date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Francis Tolentino]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref name=\"interaksyonOfficialsIssuingApologies\"/><ref name=\"philstarTolentino\">{{Cite news |last=Luna |first=Franco |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322120108/http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2020/03/22/2002723/tolentino-tests-negative-covid-19-despite-doh-guideline-not-test-if-asymptomatic|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2020/03/22/2002723/tolentino-tests-negative-covid-19-despite-doh-guideline-not-test-if-asymptomatic |title=Tolentino tests negative for COVID-19 despite DOH guideline not to test if asymptomatic |archive-date=March 22, 2020 |publisher=[[Philippine Star]] |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"mbSixMoreSenators\" />\n:Said that his testing kit did not come from the DOH. Took the test believing he has been exposed to a person who tested positive for COVID-19 and began exhibiting symptoms.<ref name=\"No to VIP testing \" /><ref name=\"vipsenatorclarify\"/>\n* [[Juan Miguel Zubiri]]&nbsp;\u2013 positive<ref name=\"interaksyonDOHTriageSystem\" /><ref name=\"interaksyonPoliticiansFamilies\"/><ref name=\"philstarZubiriPositive\">{{cite news |last1=Cabico |first1=Gaea Katreena |title=Migz Zubiri tests positive for COVID-19 |url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2020/03/16/2001414/migz-zubiri-tests-positive-covid-19 |publisher=[[Philippine Star]] |date=March 16, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"inqBulacanMayor\" />\n: The first national-level elected official to test positive in the Philippines. Tested despite being asymptomatic. Suspected to be a [[false positive]] by Health Secretary Duque who would have Zubiri tested again if not for the limited stock of testing kits.\n\n==== House of Representatives ====\n* [[Paolo Duterte]]&nbsp;\u2013 {{Abbr|{{small|TBA}}|to be announced}}<ref name=\"manilaTimesDuterteFamily\" /><ref name=\"presidentialfamily\"/>\n* [[Eric Go Yap]]&nbsp;\u2013 negative<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/256135-ritm-says-congressman-eric-yap-remains-negative-coronavirus-covid-19|title='Clerical oversight': RITM says congressman Yap 'remains negative' for COVID-19|publisher=Rappler|date=March 27, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"RITM_Yap\">{{cite web |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1249618/ritm-says-lawmaker-initially-positive-for-covid-19-doesnt-have-virus|title=RITM says Rep. Yap negative for COVID-19, admits 'clerical oversight'|publisher=The Philippine Daily Inquirer|last=Lalu|first=Gabriel 